node.text:

node.text:
The number of hours of proper practice that some researchers believe it takes to become an expert at anything. I'm nowhere near there yet. It takes passion and dedication to achieve success in any given field, and the more you enjoy your work or endeavour, the easier it is to put in the required time.

Thanks for watching!  New videos every week. 

To see what I’m up to during the rest of the week, please follow me on my other online channels;

Website: http://myselfreliance.com/​
Youtube: https://www.youtube.com/c/ShawnJamesMySelfReliance/

node.text: An unusually warm and sunny day allows for a winter swim in the cold waters of Georgian Bay in January.  Full video up on my @youtube channel Friday morning.

node.title: A Spectacular Winter Sunset on Lake Huron

node.text: How I built my off grid log cabin. In this video, the first in a series showing the complete build from the first cut to the last addition, I explain what logs I used, how I cut the saddle joints, what chinking recipe worked the best and how I made pine tar.

node.title: How to Build a Cheap Off Grid Log Cabin, Ep1  Buying Logs, Chink and Daub,

node.text: Following up on the attempted break-in at the log cabin, I talk about the importance of being prepared for smaller and medium sized emergencies rather than focusing on major events and catastrophes.

node.text: One of the few things I took from the old cabin to use at the new homestead was a couple of ash logs for hardwood flooring in the new cabin. This week, I milled the floor boards to give them time to dry before installing them next spring. Click on the link in my bio to watch the full @youtube video.
